1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The problem of finding a dense subgraph is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorics, which falls under the purview of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an improved approximation algorithm for the Dense K Subgraph problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of the Dense K Subgraph problem and proposes an improved approximation algorithm, which is relevant to the study of computational complexity. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The problem of finding a dense subgraph has applications in game theory, particularly in the study of network games. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The Dense K Subgraph problem can be viewed as a geometric problem, where the goal is to find a dense subgraph in a given graph. This makes it relevant to computational geometry.
